# EmailJS Configuration
# Get your credentials from https://www.emailjs.com/

# 1. Create a free account at EmailJS.com
# 2. Create an Email Service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
# 3. Create an Email Template with these variables:
#    - {{name}}
#    - {{email}}
#    - {{businessType}}
#    - {{service}}
#    - {{budget}}
#    - {{message}}
# 4. Copy your credentials below

NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_jmdigital
NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_contact
NEXT_PUBLIC_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY_HERE

# Instructions:
# - Rename this file to .env.local
# - Replace the values with your actual EmailJS credentials
# - Never commit .env.local to git (it's already in .gitignore)
